\section*{ORR}

When both PFS and OS tests are significant, \(\alpha=0.025\) will be allocated to the ORR test. If the OS test does not achieve statistical significance at IA1, the p value of the ORR test from IA1 will be compared to \(2.5 \%\) if the null hypotheses for PFS and OS are rejected at a later time.

Following Amendment 09, the pre-planned second interim analysis (IA2) is no longer required and will not be performed. This is because of the study hypotheses for PFS, OS and ORR being supported at the first interim analysis (IA1) with data cutoff of November 8, 2017. The pre-specified FA at approximately 416 OS events will be performed without multiplicity adjustment. If median OS is not adequately assessed for the pembrolizumab combination arm at the pre-specified FA, an updated analysis may be conducted with a minimum of 30 months follow-up after the last patient randomized.

\subsection*{8.9 Sample Size and Power Calculations}

This trial is well-powered for the primary and key secondary endpoints. Enrollment of 570 subjects is assumed to occur over 12 months at \(2: 1\) ratio between the experimental and control groups. The actual enrollment is 616 subjects within 13 months. With 370 PFS events at IA1, the study has \(\sim 72 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.0095 (one-sided) and \(\sim 84 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.025 (one-sided). With 468 PFS events at IA2, the study has \(\sim 90 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.0095 (one-sided) and \(\sim 96 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.025 (one-sided). The duration of PFS in the control group is assumed to follow an exponential distribution with a median of 6.5 months based on historical data. The assumed follow-up time after last patient enrolled is 13 months for IA2. An exponential dropout rate of \(0.35 \%\) per month is assumed.

With 242 deaths at IA1, the study has \(\sim 37 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.0155 (onesided) and \(\sim 47 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.025 (one-sided) when the PFS test is significant. With 332 deaths at IA2, the study has \(\sim 73 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.0155 (one-sided) and \(\sim 80 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.025 (one-sided) when the PFS test is significant. With 416 deaths at FA, the study has \(\sim 90 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.0155 (one-sided) and \(\sim 93 \%\) power for detecting a HR of 0.7 at 0.025 (one-sided) when the PFS test is significant. The duration of OS in the control group is assumed to follow an exponential distribution with a median of 13 months based on historical data. The exponential dropout rate assumed for OS is \(0.1 \%\) per month.

The sample size of 616 yields \(89 \%(\alpha=0.025)\) power to detect an ORR difference from an underlying \(45 \%\) response rate in the control group to \(60 \%\) in the experimental group, when both PFS and OS tests are significant. The approximate treatment difference required to reach the bound ( \(\triangle \mathrm{ORR}\) ) is 0.0575 .

Power and interim analysis calculations were performed using EAST 5 and the gsDesign R package.

Following Amendment 09, the pre-planned second interim analysis (IA2) is no longer required and will not be performed. This is because of the study hypotheses for PFS, OS, and ORR being supported at the first interim analysis (IA1) with data cutoff of November 8, 2017. The pre-specified FA at approximately 416 OS events will be performed without multiplicity adjustment. If median OS is not adequately assessed for the pembrolizumab combination arm at the pre-specified FA, an updated analysis may be conducted with a minimum of 30 months follow-up after the last patient randomized.

\subsection*{8.10 Subgroup Analyses and Effect of Baseline Factors}

To determine whether the treatment effect is consistent across various subgroups, the between-group treatment effect for OS, PFS, and ORR (with a nominal \(95 \% \mathrm{CI}\) ) will be estimated and plotted within each category of the following classification variables (a subgroup will not be analyzed if it includes \(<10 \%\) of the ITT population):
- Age category (<65, \(\geq 65\) years)
- ECOG Performance Scale \((0,1)\)
- Sex (female, male)
- Race (white, non-white)
- Geographic region (US, Ex US)
- Geographic region (EU, Ex EU)
- Smoking status (never, former/current)
- Brain metastasis status at baseline (yes, no)
- PD-L1 expression (unknown, TPS \(<1 \%\), or TPS \(\geq 1 \%\) )
- PD-L1 expression (unknown, TPS \(<50 \%\), or TPS \(\geq 50 \%\) )
- PD-L1 expression (unknown, TPS \(<1 \%, 1 \% \leq\) TPS \(\leq 49 \%\), or TPS \(\geq 50 \%\) )
- Platinum chemotherapy (cisplatin, carboplatin)

